Who thinks it's okay to be single for a long time?
Salim's therapist
Salim's therapist thinks time is relative and we don't need anybody to make us happy.

I‚Äôve been single for exactly 360 days.
It's an event that started in the past and still continues = the present perfect.

‚ÄúWhen I was your age, I'd already had you, and you'd already grown facial hair.‚Äù
She's not happy he's single and has no children.

When I was your age, (...) - first
(...) I'd already had children. - second

We don‚Äôt need anybody to make us happy.
We need "don't" for a negative sentence in the present simple.

He finds it difficult to believe his therapist 
because she's in a happy relationship with children.

It‚Äôd be easier to believe her advice if she didn‚Äôt have pictures of her family everywhere.
It's the second conditional, an unreal condition in the present = if +past simple.

It‚Äôd be easier to believe. - would
I'd already had children. - had
The second conditional = "It would be easier". 
The past perfect = "I had already had children".

