6. Expressing empathy
Learn expressions to show and react to empathy

I'm so sorry for your loss.
In this sentence, "to be sorry" is used 
to express empathy, not apologies.

I've heard about your grandmother. I'm so sorry for your loss.
We say "I'm sorry for your loss" to express empathy 
with a person who lost somebody important to them.

I'm so sorry you had to go through that.
We say "I'm so sorry you had to go through that" 
to express empathy with someone who has experienced 
a difficulty.

I know there was flooding in your area. 
I'm so sorry your family had to go through that.

The phrasal verb "to go through" means 
to experience a difficult situation.

I'm here for you.
If you need anything, I'm here for you.
We say "I'm here for you" to say we're available 
and willing to help.

If you need to talk, I'm here for you.
We say "I'm here for you" to say we're available 
and willing to help.

I appreciate that.
Michael, you've been very kind. I appreciate that.
We say "I appreciate that" if we are grateful 
to somebody for something they did or said.

I appreciate your kind words.

I'm so sorry for your loss. Showing empathy
I appreciate that. Reacting to empathy

We use "I'm so sorry for your loss / 
you had to go through that" to show empathy 
and respond using "I appreciate that".

It means a lot to me.
Silvia, you've supported me at work and 
it means a lot to me.

We say "It means a lot to me" when we feel grateful for something.

It means a lot to me. I appreciate that.
I'm so sorry for your loss.
I'm so sorry you had to go through that.

"I'm so sorry for your loss" = show empathy; 
"I appreciate that" / 
"It means a lot to me" = respond to empathy.

He was discriminated against.

He was treated badly because of his background 
and discrimination is not right.

I'm here|am here to support you.
We say "I'm here for you" to say we're available 
and willing to help.

Thanks, it means a lot to me.
We say "It means a lot to me" when we feel grateful for something.

VOCABULARY
I'm so sorry for your loss.

I'm so sorry you had to go through that.

I'm here for you.

I appreciate that.

It means a lot to me.

