7. Developing fluency
Practise expressing empathy

We say "I'm so sorry for your loss" and 
"I'm here for you" to show empathy.

I heard about Luna. I'm so sorry for your loss.
We say "I'm sorry for your loss" to express empathy 
with a person who lost somebody important to them.

If you need to talk, I'm here for you.
We say "I'm here for you" to say we're available and willing to help.

Mi Kyong's friend suffered from strong headaches 
and Mi Kyong is showing her empathy.

I'm so sorry you have to go through all that pain.

The phrasal verb "to go through" means to experience a difficult situation.

If there's anything I can do, I'm here to support you .
We say "I'm here to support you" to say 
we're available and willing to help.

I'm here to support you.
In this sentence, "to support" means "to help".





























































































































































































